PROBLEM 27
QUADRATIC PRIMES

Euler discovered the remarkable quadratic formula:
It turns out that the formula will produce 40primes for the consecutive integer values
0 <= n <= 39

however when n^2 = 40, 40^2 + 40 + 41 = 40(40 + 1) + 41 is divisibel by 41
and certainly when n = 41, 41^2 + 41 + 41 is clearly divisible by 41

the incredible formula n^2 - 79n + 1601 was discovered which procudes 80 primes for the consecutive
values 0 <= n <= 79. the product of the coefficients, -79 and 1601 is -126479

considering quadratics of the form

n^2 + an + b where |a| < 1000 and |b| <= 1000

where |n| is the modulus/absolute value of n
eg |11| = 11 and |-4| = 4


answer:
let me understand the question

i have formula n^2 + an + b
a and b are fixed constatnt i can choose
then i plug n = 0,1,2,3,.. and check how long i get consec primes before formula produce a non prime

eg
n=0 -> prime?
n=1 -> prime?
... keep going till iget non prime

so i ned to try every combination of a and b , find which produces longest
and return the a * b

sub problems to solve:
- prime check helper
- outer loop -> fix (a,b)
- inner loop -> increment n for each


|#

; a number is prime if its divisibel only by 1 and itself
; number -> boolean
(define (is-prime? n)
  (define (loop curr-n curr-fact)
    (cond [(> curr-fact (sqrt n)) #t] ;prime
          [(zero? (remainder curr-n curr-fact)) #f] ;not prime
          [else (loop curr-n (+ curr-fact 1))] ; keep trying
          )
    )
  ;initialize curr-fact to 2
  (if (< n 2)
      #f
      (loop n 2)      
      )
  )
(is-prime? 0)
(is-prime? 1)
(is-prime? 3)
(is-prime? 7)

;So for each (a, b) pair you get a score — how long the run lasted
;You want to find which (a, b) pair gives the highest score, then return a × b.

; executes the quadratic equation given n, a, b
; number number number -> number
(define (f-quad n a b)
  (+ (sqr n) (* a n) b )
  )

;for this fixed a and b, keep incrementing n from 0 until the formula produces a non-prime,
;then return how many primes you got.
; number number -> number
(define (count-primes-in-quad a b)
  (define (loop curr-n result)
    (cond [(not (is-prime? (f-quad curr-n a b))) result] ; non-prime, stop
          [else (loop (+ curr-n 1) (+ 1 result)) ]
          )
    )
  (loop 0 0)
  )

; given  a value , find the proudct of coefficient a and b for the qdr expr
; that produces max num of primes for conesc values of nn starting n = 0
(define (quadratic-primes)
  ; fix a b -> count how many consecutive primes -> store in score
  ; curr a range is -999 - 999, curr-b is from -1000 to 1000
  ; base case, stop when curr-a and curr-b reaches its max ceiling, return best-so-far
  (define (loop curr-a curr-b best-a best-b best-count-so-far)
    (cond [(and (> curr-a 999) (> curr-b 1000)) (* best-a best-b)] ;base case
          [(> curr-b 1000) (loop (+ curr-a 1) -1000 best-a best-b best-count-so-far)] ;increment a, reset b
          [else (let ((curr-count (count-primes-in-quad curr-a curr-b)))
                  (if(> curr-count best-count-so-far)
                     (loop curr-a (+ 1 curr-b) curr-a curr-b curr-count) ;update best
                     (loop curr-a (+ 1 curr-b) best-a best-b best-count-so-far) ;keep and recurse
                     )
                  
                  )]
          )
    )
  (loop -999 -1000 -999 -1000 0)
  )
(quadratic-primes)